  , issueBody =
      Just
        "This is a follow up of https://github.com/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/4572 .\n\nThe default settings for TCP keepalive on Linux mean that we won't detect connection loss until 11 minutes have passed.\n\n> http://stackoverflow.com/a/14855726/2413884 has an overview of how to set the available options from Python on Linux and OS X, and it also has a link to Windows' documentation on the topic.\n> \n> It looks like we could tune the timeout parameters on Python, though it wouldn't be portable (i.e. we would need different code for different platforms).\n> \n> In the long term, we can either implement our own protocol-level heartbeat, or add code to set the TCP keepalive parameters on a per-platform basis. For node.js there might be a way of doing it with https://www.npmjs.com/package/raw-socket .\n"
